# Prisma Conventions

- Use Prisma as the primary database access layer.
- Keep data access logic inside `modules/<module-name>/` to match module ownership.
- Avoid scattering direct Prisma queries across unrelated app files.

# Client and Query Patterns

- Use a shared Prisma client entry point instead of creating many client instances.
- Keep queries close to module use cases and name functions after domain intent.
- Prefer explicit selects/includes over fetching broad records by default.

# Transactions and Writes

- Use transactions for multi-step writes that must stay consistent.
- Validate input before database writes.
- Handle known Prisma errors and return module-level errors/messages.

# Migrations

- Use descriptive migration names focused on the schema change intent.
- Keep schema and migration changes in sync in the same change set.
- Do not edit historical migrations after they are applied in shared environments.
